---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const lastUpdated = "June 23, 2025";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy policy for calpercentage.com. We do not collect personal data, sell information, or use advertising cookies. All calculations run locally in your browser. Read our full privacy policy."
>
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-5 py-16 sm:py-24">

    <p class="form-label mb-4">Legal</p>
    <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-semibold text-ink mb-4" style="letter-spacing:-0.05em; line-height:1.1;">
      Privacy Policy
    </h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-muted mb-12">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

    <div style="border-top:1px solid var(--color-line); padding-top:3rem;" class="space-y-10">

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing:-0.02em;">Overview</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mb-3">
          calpercentage.com is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains what information we collect, why we collect it, how it is used, and what rights you have in relation to your data. We have written this policy in plain language so that anyone — not just lawyers — can understand exactly how we handle information.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mb-3">
          The short version: <strong class="text-ink">we do not collect personal data, we do not sell your information to anyone, and all percentage calculations run entirely in your browser</strong>. Your numbers never reach our servers.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6">
          calpercentage.com is a free utility website providing online percentage calculators. The nature of the site — a browser-based calculation tool with no user accounts, no purchases, and no user-generated content — means we have very little reason to collect personal information in the first place. Our approach to privacy is built on data minimization: we only receive information that is technically unavoidable when you visit any website, and we use it only to keep the site running correctly.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing:-0.02em;">Information we do not collect</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mb-3">
          To be explicit about our data minimization approach, here is a list of information we do <em>not</em> collect from visitors:
        </p>
        <ul class="text-sm text-secondary leading-7 space-y-2 list-disc pl-5">
          <li><strong class="text-ink">No personal identifiers</strong> — no names, email addresses, usernames, or account information. There are no user accounts on this site.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink">No calculation data</strong> — every number you enter into any calculator runs entirely in your browser and is never transmitted to our servers. We cannot see what you calculated.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink">No payment information</strong> — the site is completely free with no purchases, subscriptions, or payment flows of any kind.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink">No precise location data</strong> — we do not use GPS, Wi-Fi triangulation, or any other method to determine your specific physical location.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink">No behavioral profiling</strong> — we do not build profiles of individual users, track you across other websites, or participate in behavioral advertising networks.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink">No biometric data</strong> — we do not collect fingerprints, facial recognition data, voice prints, or any other biometric identifiers.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink">No sensitive personal data</strong> — we do not collect racial or ethnic origin, political opinions, religious beliefs, health data, or financial account details.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing:-0.02em;">Information we may collect automatically</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mb-3">
          Like virtually all websites, our hosting infrastructure automatically receives certain technical information when your browser connects to our servers. This is a standard feature of how the internet works, not a deliberate data collection practice on our part.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mb-3">This technical information may include:</p>
        <ul class="text-sm text-secondary leading-7 space-y-2 list-disc pl-5">
          <li><strong class="text-ink">IP address</strong> — used to route traffic to your browser. This may be logged in anonymized or aggregated form by our hosting provider.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink">Browser type and version</strong> — used to understand how to serve the site correctly to different browsers and rendering engines.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink">Operating system</strong> — used in aggregate to inform compatibility and testing decisions.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink">Pages visited and time spent</strong> — used in aggregate to understand which calculators are most useful to visitors.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink">Referring URL</strong> — the web page you visited immediately before calpercentage.com, if applicable.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink">Date and time of visit</strong> — used to analyze overall traffic patterns and uptime.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink">Country or region</strong> — derived from IP in anonymized, aggregate form to understand where our visitors are located.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mt-3">
          This data is processed only in anonymized or aggregated form to help us understand site traffic and diagnose technical issues. It is never sold, rented, or shared with third parties for marketing or advertising purposes. Individual records are not used to identify, contact, or profile any specific visitor.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing:-0.02em;">Cookies and local storage</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mb-3">
          We take a minimal approach to browser storage. Here is exactly what we store and why:
        </p>
        <ul class="text-sm text-secondary leading-7 space-y-3 list-disc pl-5">
          <li>
            <strong class="text-ink">Theme preference (localStorage)</strong> — We store a single value called <code class="text-xs font-mono bg-canvas-soft-2 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">theme</code> in your browser's <code class="text-xs font-mono bg-canvas-soft-2 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">localStorage</code> to remember whether you prefer dark or light mode across visits. This value is stored only on your device, never sent to our servers, and is not accessible by any third party.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mt-3">
          We do <strong class="text-ink">not</strong> use analytics session cookies, persistent tracking cookies, tracking pixels, browser fingerprinting, or any other cross-site tracking technologies. If you clear your browser's local storage, your theme preference will simply reset to the default light mode — no other data is affected.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing:-0.02em;">Analytics</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mb-3">
          We use Google Analytics (Google Tag Manager, measurement ID G-HKDHEPLWN2) to collect anonymized, aggregated data about how visitors use the site. This helps us understand how many people use the site, which calculators are most popular, what devices and browsers are most common, and where traffic originates.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mb-3">
          Google Analytics processes data under Google's own Privacy Policy. We have configured our Google Analytics implementation to:
        </p>
        <ul class="text-sm text-secondary leading-7 space-y-2 list-disc pl-5">
          <li>Not collect personally identifiable information.</li>
          <li>Not share data with Google for advertising or remarketing purposes.</li>
          <li>Restrict data processing to aggregate usage insights only, used solely for site improvement.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mt-3">
          You can opt out of Google Analytics tracking across all websites by installing the <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" class="text-ink underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on</a>, available free from Google.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing:-0.02em;">How we use information</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mb-3">
          The limited, anonymized information we have access to is used exclusively for the following purposes:
        </p>
        <ul class="text-sm text-secondary leading-7 space-y-2 list-disc pl-5">
          <li>Diagnosing and resolving technical issues with the site's performance or availability.</li>
          <li>Understanding in aggregate which calculators and features are most valuable to visitors.</li>
          <li>Monitoring overall site health, uptime, and traffic levels.</li>
          <li>Making informed product decisions about which new tools to build or existing tools to improve.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mt-3">
          We do not use any information to send marketing emails, display targeted advertisements, build individual user profiles, or sell data to third parties. We do not monetize visitor data in any form.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing:-0.02em;">Data retention</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mb-3">
          Because calpercentage.com does not collect personal data, there is no personal data to retain, manage, or delete on request.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6">
          Aggregated, anonymized analytics data is retained in Google Analytics for up to 14 months by default, after which it is automatically purged. Server log data retained by our hosting provider (Vercel) is handled according to their own data retention policies. The single item stored on your device — your theme preference in <code class="text-xs font-mono bg-canvas-soft-2 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">localStorage</code> — persists until you clear your browser storage or reset it yourself.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing:-0.02em;">Security</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mb-3">
          calpercentage.com is served exclusively over HTTPS, which encrypts all data in transit between your browser and our servers. Since all calculations run locally in your browser and no personal data is stored on our servers, the risk surface for a data breach is minimal by design.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6">
          We keep site dependencies and hosting infrastructure updated to address known security vulnerabilities promptly. Our hosting provider (Vercel) maintains enterprise-grade infrastructure security on our behalf. If you discover a security issue with the site, please report it via our contact page and we will investigate immediately.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing:-0.02em;">Children's privacy</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6">
          calpercentage.com is a free, publicly available utility website with no user registration, no user-generated content, and no collection of personal information. The site is appropriate for use by people of all ages, including school-age students. We do not knowingly collect any personal information from children under 13 (or under 16 in jurisdictions where that threshold applies under GDPR). If you believe a child has somehow submitted personal information to us via our contact form, please notify us immediately and we will delete it promptly.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing:-0.02em;">Your rights</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mb-3">
          Depending on where you are located, you may have certain rights regarding your personal data under applicable laws, including the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) in the European Union, the UK GDPR, or the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA). These rights may include:
        </p>
        <ul class="text-sm text-secondary leading-7 space-y-2 list-disc pl-5">
          <li><strong class="text-ink">Right of access</strong> — the right to request a copy of any personal data we hold about you.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink">Right to erasure</strong> — the right to request deletion of your personal data ("right to be forgotten").</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink">Right to rectification</strong> — the right to have inaccurate personal data corrected.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink">Right to object</strong> — the right to object to certain types of data processing, including direct marketing.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink">Right to data portability</strong> — the right to receive your data in a structured, machine-readable format.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink">Right to restriction</strong> — the right to request that we limit how we use your data under certain circumstances.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink">Right to opt out of sale (CCPA)</strong> — the right to opt out of the sale of your personal information. We do not sell personal information.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mt-3">
          Because calpercentage.com does not collect personal data, most of these rights do not apply in practice — there is simply no personal data for us to access, correct, delete, or export. However, if you have any concerns or wish to exercise any right that may be relevant, please contact us and we will respond promptly and transparently.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing:-0.02em;">Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6">
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time as the site evolves or as legal and regulatory requirements change. Any material changes will be reflected on this page with an updated "Last updated" date at the top of the document. We encourage you to review this page periodically to stay informed about how we protect your privacy. Continued use of the site after changes are posted constitutes your acceptance of the revised policy.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing:-0.02em;">Contact</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mb-4">
          If you have any questions, concerns, or requests relating to this Privacy Policy or how we handle data, please reach out via our contact page. We aim to respond to all privacy-related inquiries within 5 business days.
        </p>
        <a href="/contact" class="btn-secondary">Contact us</a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
